<span class="displaytext"><b>"sunday's our view: nonpareil endorses (candidate last)" <br/> <em>the daily nonpareil</em> [council bluffs, ia] <br/> editorial <br/> december 30, 2007</b> <p>"our position: (candidate last) excels over all other (PARTY NAME) candidates. </p><p>"at no time in recent memory has this nation faced a greater array of formidable, complex and potentially dangerous challenges. the very nature of those complex challenges and the potential means of addressing them is a recipe for divisiveness. as americans continue their search for a new commander-in-chief, they should search for an individual with vision, intellect and experience. </p><p>"in a (PARTY NAME) presidential field that boasts a host of candidates who bring a wide range of talents and experience to the table, we think former massachusetts gov. (candidate full) rises to the top as the best choice to lead his party toward the 2008 election." </p><p>... </p><p>"while all experiences point to what we feel would be a successful term in the white house, (candidate last)'s four years as governor of massachusetts, a solidly (PARTY NAME) state, underscore his potential for leading this nation. those four years demonstrate his understanding of economic principles, the intricacies of reform and, most of all, his understanding of the need to work with those on the other side of the political aisle. </p><p>"both the economy and the budget in massachusetts were in better shape at the end of (candidate last)'s term than at the beginning, and the state had made significant strides in the areas of education and health care. </p><p>"those results were not (candidate last)'s alone, but they were, in our view, the result of his vision and his leadership. </p><p>"(PARTY NAME)s need to think not only about a candidate who can win but also about a candidate who has the ability – the track record – to actually run the country if they win. </p><p>"that person is, in our opinion, (candidate full)." </p><p><em>